    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document is a survey of Performance Enhancing Proxies (PEPs) often employed to improve degraded TCP performance caused by characteristics of specific link environments, for example, in satellite, wireless WAN, and wireless LAN environments.  This memo provides information for the Internet community.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
